    {
      "id": "post-dictionary-authoring-ui-product-split",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Product Split",
      "position": {
        "x": 1380,
        "y": -140
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Product Split\n\nThe LLM can create and revise graph structure through discussion.\n\nThe paid/editor surface should focus on what the LLM cannot honestly do for itself:\n\n- GitHub and local-file access\n- browser and system integration\n- one-click layout, refinement, and repair\n- faster inspection and override control\n\nSo the toolbar is not mainly a primitive factory. It is a privileged editor surface.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
